## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| **Critical** | 1 (systemic — affects 10/10 tests) |
| High | 0 |
| Medium | 1 |
| Low | 1 |

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class. Every public method on `ProductCatalog` is called (giving ~95% line coverage), but almost nothing is actually verified. These tests cannot catch regressions.

---

### 🔴 Critical: Systematic Coverage Touching (No Real Assertions)

**Pattern:** 10 tests methodically invoke every method on `ProductCatalog`. Six have **zero assertions**; four use only `Assert.IsNotNull(result)` — a trivial check that doesn't verify correctness.

| Test Method | Assertion | What It Misses |
|---|---|---|
| `AddProduct_Works` (L17) | None | Never checks product was persisted |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` (L33) | None | Never checks price actually changed |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` (L39) | None | Never checks product was deleted |
| `GetProductCount_Works` (L64) | None | Never checks count value |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (L69) | None | Never checks prices were reduced |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` (L85) | None | Never checks products were imported |
| `GetProduct_Works` (L25) | `IsNotNull` | Doesn't verify SKU, Name, or Price |
| `SearchProducts_Works` (L47) | `IsNotNull` | Doesn't verify list contents or count |
| `GetAllProducts_Works` (L55) | `IsNotNull` | Doesn't verify list contents or count |
| `ExportToCsv_Works` (L77) | `IsNotNull` | Doesn't verify CSV content |

**Why it's Critical:** `UpdatePrice` could save the *old* price, `ApplyBulkDiscount` could multiply instead of discount, `ImportFromCsv` could silently swallow parse errors — all tests would still pass green.

**Fix — representative examples:**

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_PersistsProduct()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);

    var retrieved = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", retrieved?.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, retrieved?.Price);
}

[TestMethod]
public void UpdatePrice_ChangesStoredPrice()
{
    _catalog.AddProduct(new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m));
    _catalog.UpdatePrice("SKU-001", 14.99m);

    var updated = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual(14.99m, updated?.Price);
}

[TestMethod]
